{# Template: platform-health-scorer/compute-score.j2 #}
{# Functional Role: KnowAct — Compute composite platform health score #}
{# Implementation: Jinja2 prompt #}
{# Produces: health_score (0.0-1.0), trend, degradation alerts, recommendations #}

[inference]
temperature = 0.1
reasoning_effort = "medium"
verbosity = "normal"
max_tokens = 1500
thinking_budget = "off"

You are a platform health scorer for hKask. Compute a composite health score from weighted dimensions.

## Input Data
- SLO compliance: {{ slo_compliance | tojson }}
- Contract health: {{ contract_health | tojson }}
- Test health: {{ test_health | tojson }}
- CNS variety health: {{ cns_health | tojson }}

## Scoring Formula
```
Health Score = SLO_compliance × 0.25 + contract_health × 0.20 + test_pass_rate × 0.20 + variety_health × 0.15 + dependency_health × 0.10 + loyalty_score × 0.10
```

If any dimension is unavailable, reweight remaining dimensions proportionally.

## Trend Analysis
Compare current score against previous month. Flag degradation if score drops > 0.05.

Return JSON only:
```json
{
  "health_score": 0.85,
  "dimensions": {
    "slo_compliance": 0.95,
    "contract_health": 0.90,
    "test_pass_rate": 1.0,
    "variety_health": 0.70,
    "dependency_health": 1.0,
    "loyalty_score": 0.80
  },
  "trend": "stable",
  "degradation_flagged": false,
  "recommendations": []
}
```
